A brave mum who posted pictures of her postpregnancy stretchmarks on Instagram was horrified after they were removed for breaching the site's decency guidelinesHannah Moore 20 uploaded the snaps in a bid to boost her confidence and told her followers that &quotnobody should be judged by their size because everyone is beautiful&quotBut only two minutes later the mum of twins claims her account was deleted because the images were deemed to contain inappropriate &quotnudity and violence&quotHannah says the blocking of her account has made her think her body is &quotclearly fat ugly and disgusting and it made <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">people</a> feel sick&quot She said &quotTwo minutes after the picture was uploaded my account got closed down my mouth just dropped and my eyes watered&quotI don't know why it was out of the blue but I decided to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Post" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Post" target="_blank">post</a> a picture of my belly on Instagram because I've had twins&quotI had written underneath the picture how unconfident I had always been how relationships have been hard and how hard it is to find clothes that I like&quotI want not just myself but other women thin or bigger to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Love" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Love" target="_blank">love</a> themselves and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Love" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Love" target="_blank">love</a> their size because everyone is beautiful &quotInstagram should be more careful in whose accounts they delete and look into it further &quotHannah of Broxburn in West Lothian suffered from stretch marks after giving birth to twin girls Lily and Grace with fiance David Johnstone 22 in June last yearShe posted the pictures on Wednesday but her account was immediately shut down&quotI basically wrote that <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">people</a> should never get judged for the size and what they look like because everyone is beautiful&quot she said&quotThe picture was up two minutes until my Instagram logged out itself and then it came up saying my account has been shut down because of violations &quotNobody could get on my Instagram and nobody could search for it so someone had obviously reported the picture for nudity and all it was was a picture of my belly and it has just took my confidence away&quotIt was just me that nobody should ever get judged no matter what size they are&quotI felt so confident posting the picture showing my baby belly my belly that carried twin girls for only six months&quotInstagram's community guidelines state &quotWe know that there are <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Times" target="_blank">times</a> when <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">people</a> might want to share nude images that are artistic or creative in nature but for a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Variety_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Variety_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">variety</a> of reasons we don't allow nudity on Instagram&quotPhotos of postmastectomy scarring and women actively breastfeeding are allowed&quotBut Hannah believes she is not in breach of these guidelines despite her account being shut downHannah who was bullied during school for her weight has been left with no confidenceShe added &quotIt made me think that my body is clearly fat ugly and disgusting and it made <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">people</a> feel sick&quotI wrote that no one should ever get judged or brought down by their size because it shouldn't matter&quotNow that nice weather is here I still feel that I need to cover myself up I can't go out without covering my arms or legs I just feel like <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_%28magazine%29" target="_blank">people</a> are looking at me and are disgusted&quotA spokeswoman for Instagram did not wish to comment but said &quotIt was a technical mistake and the account has been restored&quot Try your hand at our news quiz 
